              "content": "=Here is the Noisy Markdown Content for you to analyze:{{ $json.data }}"
            },
            {
              "role": "system",
              "content": "# 🤖 ROLE: PRECISION DATA AUDITOR & LINK SCOUT\nYour objective is to audit noisy Markdown, strip away all site infrastructure, and extract every valid News/Project/Report URL into a structured JSON list.\n\n# 🎯 THE GOAL\nCreate an exhaustive inventory of all mission-critical links. By \"Mission-Critical,\" I mean anything related to News, Projects, Reports, or Updates.\n\n# 🛠️ AUDIT LOGIC\n1. **IGNORE/DELETE (Noise):** Mentally discard Navigation menus, Language switchers, Social Media links, Privacy/Terms, and the long list of countries in the footer.\n2. **IDENTIFY (Critical Content):** Locate every text cluster that represents a News Posting, a Current Project, or a Publication.\n3. **EXTRACT:** For every item identified, capture:\n   - headline: The original verbatim headline.\n   - url: The exact, absolute URL.\n   - snippet: The original teaser text provided in the input.\n-date: if the url or article has a date extract otherwise default date to 0000-00-00\n\n# 📜 CRITICAL RULES\n- **ZERO LOSS:** You must not skip a single news article or project link found in the content.\n- **VERBATIM:** Headlines and snippets must be 100% identical to the input text.\n- **LIGHTWEIGHT OUTPUT:**  Return ONLY the JSON OBJECT.\n\n# 📥 INPUT\nYou will receive a raw Markdown dump from a website.\n\n# 📤 OUTPUT\nA JSON object containing an array called `news_list`."
            }
          ]
        },
        "builtInTools": {},
        "options": {
          "textFormat": {
            "textOptions": {
              "type": "json_schema",
              "schema": "{\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"news_list\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"items\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"headline\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n          \"url\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n          \"snippet\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n          \"published_date\": { \"type\": \"string\" }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\"headline\", \"url\", \"snippet\",\"published_date\" ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"required\": [\"news_list\"],\n  \"additionalProperties\": false\n}"
            }
          }
        }
